history.content:
There certainly isn't a "right" answer to this one, but if I had to choose one of the two, I would probably recommend taking 16B first.  The main reasons for this are that (1) 16B is a somewhat broader intro course, so it would open more doors for you (61C opens doors to classes as well, but less broadly so), and (2) 16B covers at a somewhat more basic level some material that also shows up in 61C.  (There are no changes in 61C planned/expected because of this, but over the long term, we expect that people will in all likelihood have taken 16B before or at most concurrently with 61C.)

I'm not sure about a 61C alternate final, but will ping the instructors to ask.

I am an EECS sophomore who has not taken CS61C or EE16B and does not have a strong preference of CS vs EE yet. I was wondering if I had to choose which would be more beneficial to take first.

Also, is there an update on whether CS61C could offer another final time for people taking both EE16B and CS61C?

Thanks!
history.subject: CS61C vs EE16B next semester
